Explanation:
We use a loop to iterate from 1 to n, and for each iteration, we use another loop to check if the current number is divisible by any of the prime factors (2, 3, 5). If it is, we multiply the current number by itself and divide it by the corresponding prime factor. This process continues until we find the nth ugly number. Since we only have a single loop, the time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the result variable.

